    "caption": "Woolly, sharp-eyed, and surprisingly good at recognizing faces.",
    "shortDescription": "Sheep can recognize up to fifty different sheep faces — and remember them for years. They also recognize human faces and can tell when someone looks happy versus grumpy from a photograph. Their wool grows continuously and must be shorn, or it can grow so heavy it makes it hard for them to move. Fun fact: Sheep have excellent peripheral vision and can see nearly all the way around their head without turning — but they have a blind spot directly behind them."
